ely short for boss-killing.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Shadex,</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
 I understand that.  People do like to compare aas class to class.  Unfortunately, your point made me think of something else which I'm gonna write about instead of going to bed heh..<br>
<br>
Class aa abilities do not exist in isolation of each other, the player, and others.  When you look at an AA you need to look at what it does for that class.  What advantages and disadvantages does a <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>wizard</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> with manaburn have over a <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>wizard</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> without manaburn?  Note that except for Xuzl(Rage of Zomm Clone), everything a wizard does requires mana in rather large amounts.  Losing all of your mana is a much bigger deal for a wizard than for a magician.  Also realize that using manburn to deal those huge damage numbers requires a full bar of mana.  That means you can't be using any of your mana reserves before you manaburn.  <br>
<br>
If a wizard, mid fight, suddenly saw the need to manaburn and only had 1500 mana, he'd be a lot better off casting sunstrike or draughts.  If he knew he'd be called on to manaburn, then he'd be unable to contribute much early in the fight, to say nothing about his contribution afterwards.  These sorts of things are easily forgotten when you look at the manaburn ability in isolation from the actual wizard class and how it is really played in everquest.<br>
<br>
Dire Charm is a great tool but rather difficult to use in many situations.  A dire pet can also die or be dispelled, last I knew.  A great solo ability to be sure, but it carries the old and hated pet XP penalty..<br>
<br>
Chaotic Stab I'm not too familiar with..  but the one rogue I know with the ability is rather disappointed with it.  It doesn't help damage much at all when the rogue is getting mostly full backstabs anyway.  Also remember that it is the rogue's lot in life to deal damage.  Unlike a magician, a rogue usually has little else to do.   As a rogue I would expect to have a class ability that would directly increase my damage output.  Chaotic Stab is nice, but it's really only abating the negative effects of a mob facing you.  You'll never see big improvements in max damage ability from Chaotic Stab.  <br>
<br>
Compare those to Frenzied Burnout, which can be activated at will whenever you are using a pet and immediately starts doing extra damage.  The only drawback being that BO is overwritten(which does suck imo).  Unlike Dire Charm it is not dependant on many factors to be able to use.  Unlike Manaburn there are few serious drawbacks to using it.  Unlike Chaotic Stab it raises your maximum damage potential(and C.S. is also situational like Dire Charm).<br>
<br>
When you put Frenzied Burnout next to a more detailed comparison of the other class abilities, it doesn't seem quite so horrible anymore.  I'm not saying this is a perfect comparison, nor am I trying to justify leaving FB as it is.  I do think trying to be as fair as possible in our comparisions, however, will benefit us more in the long run.<br>
<br>
I think ihe original poster had a good idea in comparing the mana values of each ability.  Since mana use is a common trait between many classes, it would seem to be a fair basis for comparison, and in some ways this comparison is certianly quite useful.  Unfortunately, mana regen doesn't determine all class abilities or all in-game actions, which was what I addressed before. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugoladus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goladus</A> at: 9/9/02 8:39:09 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=pissed1vi2soe>Pissed1VI2SOE</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 330<br> <font color=#333333>(9/9/02 5:12:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=366.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   FB math - numbers speculation - Also for don't address VI</span><hr size=1> Why not just make the haste's stack?<br>
<br>
Unbuffed Normal Pet=100% (meaning 100% of normal speed)<br>
<br>
BOIV+MM=65% haste(?, all I know is cast on pet every 15 minutes)<br>
<br>
FBO=99% haste<br>
<br>
Which would result in 264% (100% normal speed, 164% haste).<br>
<br>
Even at that assume a 50dps unbuffed normal pet, adding in BOIV+FBO you'd end up with 132 dps for 36 seconds or 4752 total pet dmg in that 36 seconds (which is still low for the time investment of the aaxp's).  Only a little more than than 1/3 (1/3 would be 88% haste, and I really don't feel like crunching numbers) of the total pet dmg in that 36 seconds would be attributed to FBO, which would still be less than 1700dmg attributed to FBO.  Least that would make it useable.<br>
<br>
Of course if your using a normal pet (gvoc) then your pet probably won't be at 50dps?  Which would lower all the numbers.  They could even let epics haste stack and it would be close to worth the effort.<br>
<br>
It wouldn't be tooo much to ask them to let BO and FBO to stack, since FBO is not much of a haste improvement over ABOV+mm. (assuming ABOV&gt;BOIV, can't speak from experience there).<br>
<br>
Again putting an AoE explosion at the end could result in massive agro towards the mage, is that really what you want?<br>
<br>
Putting a single target explotion (while a much safer idea) can have the same result.  Any adds that have not been mez'ed (beit unmezzable or lack of chanter) will see you doing that dmg to the target and will have a huge tendency to jump off the MA and onto a petless mage (see the effects of CH with adds, then add in that your ac cannot compare to that of a cleric, we don't have root, stun, etc,).  Even if there were no adds to potentially jump all over you, you would still be taking a huge risk of gaining too much agro.  You would be losing your ONLY defence, the explotion is uneeded and unwanted IMO.  If pet xplodes you have to resummon another one, which means FBO costs you mana, and as such should do ALOT more dmg then it does, however if it did that dmg through an explotion the agro goes to you and your gonna be FM right after your finished loading.<br>
<br>
I'll agree that on paper FBO looks like crap, but why address VI with an unfinished thought?  Your pushing them away.  We should however discuss our thoughts on how VI could improve FBO to make it a worthwhile skill, then have either Ronaldo or a board moderator send the results of that discussion to VI.  Any fix anyone can come up with is incomplete without discussion, it needs hashed, rehashed and hashed again with input from the community and obviously a reasonable solution could be formed for &quot;the better of the mage class&quot; not the better of any particular mage.  Then and only then would it be a complete thought, worthy enough to demand the attention of VI staff.  <br>
<br>
If we (as a class) want it fix'ed, we need to come to a single solution which is comparable yet modest for the amount of time invested in aaxp.  If theres 20-30 different view points on what would really be &quot;cool&quot; it would take VI staff alot longer to work out the best solution.  Also VI staff cannot take one voice as the thought of an entire class.  I admit I like the thought behind the initial poster, but I really think it needs refined, as that would still leave FBO lacking-vs-time invested, before it is addressed to VI staff. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uathao.showPublicProfile?language=EN>athao</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#333333>(9/9/02 5:50:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=366.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: FB math - numbers speculation - Also for don't address V</span><hr size=1> FBO needs to be fixed.  It is an AA skill that was given to us many months ago with the release of SoL...and it is STILL broken.<br>
