<br>
I'd do it this way though:<br>
<br>
Base pet=100% haste<br>
Base pet + muzzle + BO4 = 100+9+65= 174% haste<br>
<br>
Then have FBO modify that current haste with 99% haste<br>
<br>
174 *1.99= 346% haste<br>
<br>
Let's say on the average ubermob epic DPS is around 45-50dps with muzzle and BO4. In a normal 6 ticks (36 seconds), that would be 1,800 damage on the high end. If FBO stacked, you'd essentially double the damage just due to doubling the effective haste. That would  about 3,600 damage with 1,800 approximately attributable to FBO.<br>
<br>
I forget whether FBO has an ATK buff as well (I seem to recall it does). If so, you might be closer to 4,000 damage over that 36 second period with about 2,200 attributable to FBO then. <br>
<br>
Add in flurry (forget that damn rampage component) and you could get to the 3K incremental damage mark for FBO and NEAR 5K overall for pet damage output in that same period. I'd say that's acceptable, useful and worthwhile in my eyes.<br>
<br>
If by some miracle you had ancient: BO5, in this scenario you'd get around another 10% lift on top of that (376% haste vs. 346% with BO4). Heh, but no one on my server has BO5 or probably will for several months. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><table width=100%><tr><td width=33%><font color=blue><i><b>Master Svenuce Summonstuff</b></i></font><br>
